OperationState.description: Operational states of a router or an interface.

stnRouterUp.name: stnRouterUp
stnRouterUp.description: A stnRouterUp trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the stnRouterState object in the STN-ROUTER-MIB has transitioned to the assigned(4) state for one of its routers. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the RouterUpTraps configuration object.

stnRouterDown.name: stnRouterDown
stnRouterDown.description: A stnRouterDown trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the stnRouterState object in the STN-ROUTER-MIB has transitioned to the failedassign(7) or error(8) state for one of its routers. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the RouterDownTraps configuration object.

stnRouterReassigned.name: stnRouterReassigned
stnRouterReassigned.description: A stnRouterReassigned trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the stnRouterState object in the STN-ROUTER-MIB has transitioned to the the assigned(1) state for one of its routers. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the RouterReassignedTraps configuration object.

stnRouterReassignFailure.name: stnRouterReassignFailure
stnRouterReassignFailure.description: A stnRouterReassignFailure trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the stnRouterState object in the STN-ROUTER-MIB has transitioned to the failedassign(7) or error(8) state for one of its routers. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the RouterReassignFailureTraps configuration object.

stnSubnetIfAssignFailure.name: stnSubnetIfAssignFailure
stnSubnetIfAssignFailure.description: A stnSubnetIfAssignFailure trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the stnSubnetInterfaceState object in the STN-ROUTER-MIB has transitioned to the failedassign(7) or error(8) state for one of its interfaces. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the stnEnableSubnetInterfaceTraps configuration object.

stnConfigAuditRouterFailure.name: stnConfigAuditRouterFailure
stnConfigAuditRouterFailure.description: A stnConfigAuditRouterFailure trap signifies that the agent entity has detected an inconsistency between an active and configured routers after a failover. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the CfgAuditRouterTraps configuration object.

stnConfigAuditSubnetIfFailure.name: stnConfigAuditSubnetIfFailure
stnConfigAuditSubnetIfFailure.description: A stnConfigAuditSubnetIfFailure trap signifies that agent entity has detected an inconsistency between an active and configured subnet interface after a failover. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the CfgAuditSubnetIfTraps configuration object.

stnConfigAuditPppoeIfFailure.name: stnConfigAuditPppoeIfFailure
stnConfigAuditPppoeIfFailure.description: A stnConfigAuditPppoeIfFailure trap signifies that agent entity has detected an inconsistency between an active and configured PPPOE interface after a failover. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the CfgAuditPppoeIfTraps configuration object.

stnConfigAuditPppIfFailure.name: stnConfigAuditPppIfFailure
stnConfigAuditPppIfFailure.description: A stnConfigAuditPppIfFailure trap signifies that agent entity has detected an inconsistency between an active and configured PPP interface after a failover. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the CfgAuditPppIfTraps configuration object.
